A renewable energy firm, Royal Power and Energy Limited has unveiled brands of hybrid solar home systems, inverters and other renewable energy devices as it launches its regional office in Abuja. Speaking at the event, the Deputy Managing Director, Mr Kesavan Madhavarao said the firm has trained over 200 Nigerians on power installations as it works to complement the efforts of the federal government in providing power supply for Nigerians. He also urged government to provide a favourable business climate for investors noting that there was need for consistent policies and investment in the power sector just as India began 70 years ago to solve its electricity problems. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY The Sales Manager, Mr B. Ram Achrandram said it has dealers spread across Abuja, Kaduna, Sokoto and others parts of Nigeria. The Channels Manager, Mr Deepak Kumar, said the firm has spent 15 years in Nigeria with its head office in Lagos. He added: “We have done over 15,000 installations with products ranging from solar roof top solutions, pure sine wave Signal inverter, renewable energy battery and solar lighting equipment.”  How NEMSA pushes renewable energy growth, certifies 18 firms Clean energy: Why solar is gaining prominence in Nigeria FG to unveil National Policy on Renewable Energy